The paper deals with coding theory and channel coding, which are typically studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Communication Complexity (cs.CC) sub-categories. The use of sparse-graph codes and belief propagation also suggests a connection to the Distributed Systems (cs.DS) sub-category. The applications mentioned in the abstract (pre-coding for optics, tornado raptor codes, protograph constructions) are related to Networked Systems (cs.NI) and Signal Processing (cs.SI) sub-categories.
